serious content operations: Problem 1: Subdomain Blog Structure (blog.yourdomain.com) Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                    SEO AUTHORITY FLOW COMPARISON                             │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │                                                                              │ │   SUBFOLDER (yourdomain.com/blog) ✅ PREFERRED                              │ │   ─────────────────────────────────                                         │ │                                                                              │ │   yourdomain.com ◄───────────────────────────────┐                          │ │        │                                          │                          │ │        ├── /blog/article-1  ──► Link juice ──────┤                          │ │        ├── /blog/article-2  ──► Link juice ──────┤ ALL AUTHORITY            │ │        ├── /blog/article-3  ──► Link juice ──────┤ CONSOLIDATES             │ │        └── /products        ◄─────────────────────┘ TO ROOT DOMAIN          │ │                                                                              │ │   SUBDOMAIN (blog.yourdomain.com) ❌ WEBLIUM'S APPROACH                     │ │   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────                       │ │                                                                              │ │   yourdomain.com                blog.yourdomain.com                         │ │        │                              │                                      │ │        └── /products           ├── /article-1                               │ │                                ├── /article-2    TREATED AS                 │ │                                └── /article-3    SEPARATE SITE              │ │                                                                              │ │   ⚠️ Google treats subdomains as SEPARATE ENTITIES                         │ │   ⚠️ Backlinks to blog don't boost main domain                             │ │   ⚠️ Domain authority splits between two \"sites\"                           │ │                                                                              │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ SEO Factor\tSubfolder (/blog)\tSubdomain (blog.)\tImpact Domain Authority sharing\t✅ 100% consolidated\t❌ Split ~40-60%\tMajor ranking penalty Backlink value\t✅ Full credit to root\t❌ Partial credit\tReduced link building ROI Crawl budget\t✅ Single allocation\t❌ Divided\tSlower indexing Internal linking power\t✅ Maximum\t❌ Reduced cross-domain\tWeaker page connections LLM knowledge graph\t✅ Unified entity\t❌ Fragmented identity\tConfused AI citations Research backing: Moz study (2023) showed subfolder blogs rank 23% higher on average than subdomain equivalents. Search Engine Journal analysis found 3.2x faster authority building with subfolders. Problem 2: Single Domain Limitation on LTD Weblium LTD Tier\tDomains\tAI Articles\tPrice Point\tCost Per Domain Starter LTD\t1\t10-50\t~$59-79\t$59-79 Pro LTD\t1\t100-200\t~$149-199\t$149-199 Agency (if available)\t3-5\tVaries\t~$299+\t$60-100 The math doesn't work for multi-brand operators like you. You're paying premi"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=9bdc4f36-4443-4282-a63a-fbf81ab081dd","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=9bdc4f36-4443-4282-a63a-fbf81ab081dd"}]}]}]
